ptolemy.kernel.util

Interface IconAttribute

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActorNameIcon, AttributeValueIcon, BoxedValueIcon, BoxedValuesIcon, ConstraintMonitorIcon, CopyCatIcon, DesignPatternIcon, DynamicEditorIcon, EditorIcon, ImageIcon, KeplerXMLIcon, MonitorIcon, NameIcon, PDFIcon, ShapeIcon, StateIcon, SVGIcon, TableIcon, TextIcon, UpdatedValueIcon, ValueIcon, XMLIcon

    public interface IconAttribute
    A marker interface for an attribute that describes an icon. This interface is used to identify attributes whose purpose is only to provide a visual rendition (an icon) for an object. A host can use this interface to determine whether an object has such a visual rendition or to filter out such renditions.
    Since:
    Ptolemy II 11.0
    Author:
    Edward A. Lee
    Pt.AcceptedRating:

    Pt.ProposedRating:
